text: Iowa County is a county in the U.S. state of Wisconsin. As of 2020, 23,709 people lived there. Its county seat is Dodgeville. It is also the largest city in the county. Iowa County is part of the Madison Metropolitan Statistical Area. ==Geography== The county has a total area of .
